WEBVTT

00:22.356 --> 00:23.524
Oh, yeah!

00:23.566 --> 00:25.109
It's a fucking blackout, man!

00:43.502 --> 00:45.671
♪ I see a red door ♪

00:45.713 --> 00:49.467
♪ And I want it painted black ♪

00:49.508 --> 00:52.094
♪ No colors anymore ♪

00:52.136 --> 00:54.930
♪ I want them to turn black ♪

00:54.972 --> 00:58.601
♪ I see the girls walk by ♪

00:58.642 --> 01:01.854
♪ Dressed in their
summer clothes ♪

01:01.896 --> 01:06.233
♪ I have to turn my head
until my darkness goes ♪

01:08.277 --> 01:13.365
♪ I see a line of cars and
they're all painted black ♪

01:15.242 --> 01:19.789
♪ With flowers and my love,
both never to come back ♪

01:19.830 --> 01:22.416
♪ I see people
turn their heads ♪

01:22.458 --> 01:25.878
♪ And quickly look away ♪

01:25.920 --> 01:27.838
♪ Like a newborn baby ♪

01:27.880 --> 01:31.884
♪ It just happens every day ♪

01:31.926 --> 01:37.765
♪ I look inside myself
and see my heart is black ♪

01:37.807 --> 01:40.643
♪ I see my red door ♪

01:40.684 --> 01:43.729
♪ I must have it painted black ♪

01:43.771 --> 01:46.273
♪ Maybe then I'll fade away ♪

01:46.315 --> 01:49.652
♪ And not have
to face the facts ♪

01:49.693 --> 01:52.446
♪ It's not easy facing up ♪

01:52.488 --> 01:56.283
♪ When your whole world
is black ♪

01:56.325 --> 01:59.578
♪ No more will my green sea
go turn a deeper blue ♪

02:02.081 --> 02:05.334
♪ I could not foresee
this thing ♪

02:05.376 --> 02:08.295
♪ Happening to you... ♪

02:08.337 --> 02:09.547
It's a fucking blackout!

02:09.588 --> 02:11.048
Lights out in all five boroughs.

02:11.090 --> 02:12.842
NYPD's calling for backup.

02:12.883 --> 02:14.510
- Where?
- "Where"?!

02:14.552 --> 02:16.762
Look out the window, Salovaara...
Fucking everywhere!

02:16.804 --> 02:20.349
Well, get out there
and man the fucking streets!

02:20.391 --> 02:24.103
♪ I see a red door
and I want it ♪

02:24.144 --> 02:25.813
♪ Painted black... ♪

02:25.855 --> 02:27.147
All the boroughs
are blacked out!

02:28.524 --> 02:31.193
♪ I want them to turn black... ♪

02:31.235 --> 02:32.528
What the fuck is going on?

02:32.570 --> 02:34.029
I told you, you fool!

02:34.071 --> 02:36.240
I told you!
Any blood on those streets

02:36.282 --> 02:37.866
is on your hands!

02:37.867 --> 02:39.410
I need more than your word!

02:39.451 --> 02:41.120
I need fucking proof!

02:41.161 --> 02:42.705
"Proof"? Look, look, look!

02:42.746 --> 02:44.707
The plague is here...
Is that not proof enough?!

02:44.748 --> 02:46.000
Damn you!

02:46.041 --> 02:48.210
Listen to me.

02:48.252 --> 02:50.588
I'll tell you all I know
about the Fourth Reich,

02:50.629 --> 02:52.631
but you will take
these shackles off.

02:52.673 --> 02:54.258
I will not.
You are a criminal.

02:54.300 --> 02:56.152
- I am not a criminal. Please!
- You are a murderer.

02:56.176 --> 02:57.636
No, I'm a savior!

02:57.678 --> 03:00.347
Do you understand that?
I'm a savior!

03:00.389 --> 03:02.266
Look at that.
That's a cross.

03:02.308 --> 03:04.685
You are a woman of God, are you?

03:04.727 --> 03:05.769
Are you?!

03:05.811 --> 03:07.646
- I am.
- Yeah, okay.

03:09.440 --> 03:12.234
Darkness was only
the ninth plague.

03:12.276 --> 03:15.654
Did nuns ever teach you what
the tenth and final one was?

03:15.696 --> 03:17.364
The death of the firstborn.

03:17.406 --> 03:19.408
Death, death of millions.

03:19.450 --> 03:21.160
The death of millions.

03:21.201 --> 03:23.579
And if you hope to stop it,

03:23.621 --> 03:26.582
we must go now.

03:26.624 --> 03:29.919
This is a fucking
one-night stand.

03:29.960 --> 03:31.170
Clock strikes midnight,

03:31.211 --> 03:32.671
and I'm back
to hunting your ass.

03:32.713 --> 03:33.923
Give me your hands.

03:33.964 --> 03:35.925
Hunting me?

03:35.966 --> 03:37.760
I swear to fucking God,
you try anything,

03:37.801 --> 03:39.261
- I will shoot you.
- Yes, I'm sure.

03:49.313 --> 03:51.023
Come here!

03:58.822 --> 04:02.242
Why didn't you save me?

04:02.284 --> 04:04.119
You did this to me!

04:11.293 --> 04:13.337
It's your fault.

04:23.847 --> 04:25.265
How the bloody fuck

04:25.307 --> 04:27.434
do we know
that we can trust her?!

04:27.476 --> 04:29.120
Because if anyone
found out what I'm doing,

04:29.144 --> 04:31.063
I'd be going
on a ride 25-to-life

04:31.105 --> 04:33.482
alongside you Village People
cover band motherfuckers.

04:33.524 --> 04:34.775
- All right, stop. Enough.
- No.

04:34.817 --> 04:36.443
- Enough! Stop!
- Meyer!

04:36.485 --> 04:39.863
They just blew up
a goddamn power plant.

04:39.905 --> 04:41.782
They ravage a city.

04:41.824 --> 04:43.659
We need her.

04:43.701 --> 04:46.120
We need her resources.

04:50.040 --> 04:52.917
Where's Jonah,
and where's, uh, Murray?

04:52.918 --> 04:54.169
We got separated.

04:54.211 --> 04:55.587
And Murray ain't winning

04:55.629 --> 04:58.090
the New York City Marathon
anytime soon.

04:58.132 --> 04:59.967
And I'm-I'm fine, too,
thank you.

05:00.009 --> 05:01.760
I can feel the concern.

05:06.181 --> 05:08.559
Jonah.

05:10.519 --> 05:13.022
I'm so sorry.

05:13.063 --> 05:14.982
I'm sorry.

05:16.025 --> 05:17.901
I'm sorry.

05:20.112 --> 05:21.989
No.

05:22.031 --> 05:24.616
Oh. Oh, no.

05:28.454 --> 05:30.330
Oh, God.

05:30.372 --> 05:32.499
Today...

05:32.541 --> 05:36.336
we, too, are in total darkness,

05:36.378 --> 05:40.257
because Murray was our light.

05:40.299 --> 05:43.302
It's no secret

05:43.343 --> 05:46.680
that in the shadows
of the Shoah,

05:46.722 --> 05:49.433
Murray turned away from God,

05:49.475 --> 05:53.312
as he asked,
"How can God exist?"

05:54.563 --> 05:56.482
The irony

05:56.523 --> 05:59.610
is that the answer
to the question

05:59.651 --> 06:02.029
is Murray.

06:02.071 --> 06:04.031
A man like this

06:04.073 --> 06:08.035
is the greatest evidence
of Hashem.

06:08.077 --> 06:09.995
Not the burning bush,

06:10.037 --> 06:12.790
not the great leviathan,

06:12.831 --> 06:16.835
but a man who ushered
others to safety

06:16.877 --> 06:21.256
during that subway accident
last night.

06:21.298 --> 06:24.635
A man who came
to my office last year,

06:24.676 --> 06:26.970
unbeknownst to Mindy,

06:27.012 --> 06:29.807
and as a final gift

06:29.848 --> 06:32.518
to his faithful wife

06:32.559 --> 06:34.394
said, "Rabbi,

06:34.436 --> 06:38.941
"when she's finally succeeded
in nagging me to death,

06:38.982 --> 06:42.319
"I want the service in shul.

06:42.361 --> 06:44.822
"I want a Jewish ceremony.

06:44.863 --> 06:48.492
"Not because I believe in him,

06:48.534 --> 06:51.703
but because I believe in her."

06:54.790 --> 06:57.292
Now, forever,

06:57.334 --> 07:00.629
let us believe in Murray,

07:00.671 --> 07:05.008
for because
we have known Murray,

07:05.050 --> 07:08.762
we will forever know the light.

07:08.804 --> 07:10.806
♪ ♪

07:19.231 --> 07:22.401
♪ ♪

07:37.916 --> 07:39.918
♪ ♪

07:49.052 --> 07:50.470
I love you.

07:53.348 --> 07:56.476
♪ ♪

08:18.498 --> 08:20.876
So...

08:20.918 --> 08:22.502
Area hospitals
have no admissions

08:22.544 --> 08:24.838
for viral outbreaks,
chemical exposure.

08:24.880 --> 08:26.298
Nothing.

08:26.340 --> 08:28.383
Those bombs didn't
carry a virus.

08:28.425 --> 08:30.427
NYPD is chalking the explosion

08:30.469 --> 08:33.263
up to an electrical
malfunction on the subway.

08:33.305 --> 08:34.640
So...

08:34.681 --> 08:36.975
No virus, no mass casualties.

08:37.017 --> 08:38.810
It doesn't make sense.

08:38.852 --> 08:40.896
Maybe Murray stopped it.

08:40.938 --> 08:43.899
Maybe they just wanted
to down the power grid,

08:43.941 --> 08:46.193
blow up the subway,
kill hundreds,

08:46.235 --> 08:47.611
and we foiled it.

08:47.653 --> 08:48.862
No...

08:48.904 --> 08:50.530
We didn't foil shit.

08:50.572 --> 08:52.332
They all said The Ghost
was building a weapon

08:52.366 --> 08:53.825
more powerful than the A-bomb.

08:53.867 --> 08:55.619
The kid's right...
The Ghost's blood samples

08:55.661 --> 08:57.496
are our best lead.

08:57.537 --> 08:59.164
I'll check in with Patricia.

08:59.206 --> 09:00.958
We meet back at Meyer's.

09:28.277 --> 09:30.404
Mr. Simpson, sir?

09:30.445 --> 09:32.823
This is Officer Maldonado
with the Chevy Chase PD.

09:32.864 --> 09:35.867
Someone called in
a welfare check for you, sir.

09:35.909 --> 09:38.078
Mr. Simpson!

09:38.120 --> 09:40.330
Are you okay in there?

09:47.045 --> 09:49.464
Mr. Simpson?

09:59.057 --> 10:01.810
What the fuck?

10:01.852 --> 10:04.688
With 500,000 gallons
by the end of this week,

10:04.730 --> 10:07.899
we estimate 12 million
casualties by month's end.

10:07.941 --> 10:10.652
We'll hit every inner city
from here to Los Angeles.

10:10.694 --> 10:12.571
Low income, low IQ.

10:12.612 --> 10:14.364
Our studies show minorities
will purchase

10:14.406 --> 10:16.867
whatever poison we sell them,
as long as it's cheap.

10:16.908 --> 10:19.036
And in my day,
we thought six million

10:19.077 --> 10:20.996
was cause for celebration.

10:21.038 --> 10:23.415
Just marvelous.

10:26.168 --> 10:29.963
And the solution was
brought here safe and sound

10:30.005 --> 10:32.466
because of you.

10:32.507 --> 10:35.218
Just lovely, my dear.

10:35.260 --> 10:38.805
And yet, you...

10:38.847 --> 10:42.476
let the old Jew's rats
get away once more.

10:42.517 --> 10:43.727
I got one of them.

10:43.769 --> 10:45.520
It should've been all.

10:48.774 --> 10:52.069
Take care of the vermin
the American could not.

10:53.528 --> 10:55.822
And take him along.

10:57.532 --> 10:59.493
When a dog soils the rug,

10:59.534 --> 11:01.578
you must thrust his face
into his own shit.

11:37.656 --> 11:40.033
♪ ♪

11:52.295 --> 11:54.297
Just one, okay?

11:54.339 --> 11:56.216
- Can I have two?
- Mm-hmm.

11:56.258 --> 11:57.676
Roxy?

11:58.844 --> 12:01.221
You need to come back.

12:01.263 --> 12:03.640
Now more than ever before.

12:03.682 --> 12:05.809
Murray stopped the bomb, Meyer.

12:05.851 --> 12:08.103
No.

12:08.145 --> 12:10.814
The winds are
bringing far worse.

12:10.856 --> 12:13.733
What if Murray had been me, huh?

12:13.775 --> 12:15.694
What would she do then?

12:15.735 --> 12:17.737
Well...

12:17.779 --> 12:21.032
it will be you.

12:21.074 --> 12:23.160
And the little one.

12:23.201 --> 12:24.786
And all of us.

12:24.828 --> 12:27.205
This weapon will kill everyone.

12:27.247 --> 12:30.208
You can't save her

12:30.250 --> 12:34.337
unless you save
the world, too, darling.

12:37.632 --> 12:39.134
Why did that man say

12:39.176 --> 12:40.469
you need to save the world?

12:40.510 --> 12:41.720
He's crazy.

12:41.761 --> 12:44.598
Mommy, are you a superhero?

12:49.144 --> 12:52.731
I'm a black woman
in America, baby.

12:52.772 --> 12:56.026
Superheroes
ain't got nothing on me.

12:57.444 --> 12:59.654
Come on.

13:07.287 --> 13:10.207
Come in.

13:13.335 --> 13:15.253
Yeah, Jonah.

13:15.295 --> 13:17.130
Amy said you wanted to see me.

13:17.172 --> 13:19.007
Yeah, c-come in.

13:27.057 --> 13:29.684
I should've...
I should've stayed.

13:29.726 --> 13:31.811
- I should've stayed. I...
- Oh, no!

13:31.853 --> 13:33.647
- I should've.
- No, no, no, no, no.

13:33.688 --> 13:35.166
- I shouldn't have left.
- No, then...

13:35.190 --> 13:37.776
then would you just be lying

13:37.817 --> 13:40.737
in that coffin beside him.

13:40.779 --> 13:43.156
No. Oh, no, no.

13:43.198 --> 13:45.992
That's no place for a boy.

13:46.034 --> 13:49.246
It's just, um...

13:49.287 --> 13:51.915
I've been trying to picture

13:51.957 --> 13:54.793
his final moment.

13:56.419 --> 13:58.380
And I just...

13:58.421 --> 14:01.341
I need to know, Jonah.

14:03.218 --> 14:05.345
Was he...

14:05.387 --> 14:07.847
he afraid?

14:09.432 --> 14:11.685
No, no, no, he...

14:15.272 --> 14:18.441
He kept saying everything...

14:18.483 --> 14:21.069
everything...

14:21.111 --> 14:23.113
w-w-would be okay.

14:24.656 --> 14:28.243
He sounded like
he really meant it.

14:28.285 --> 14:30.203
Oh.

14:33.373 --> 14:35.208
He said something in Hebrew.

14:35.250 --> 14:36.501
Uh...

14:36.543 --> 14:38.587
In Hebrew?

14:38.628 --> 14:41.798
Hodu...

14:41.840 --> 14:44.259
l'Adonai?

14:47.178 --> 14:49.139
Give thanks to the Lord...

14:51.016 --> 14:53.476
for the Lord is good?

14:53.518 --> 14:54.561
Yeah.

14:54.603 --> 14:57.063
Hodu, hodu

14:57.105 --> 15:00.275
l'Adonai, l'Adonai ki tov.

15:01.318 --> 15:03.695
Um...

15:18.335 --> 15:21.046
I'm sorry.

15:40.857 --> 15:42.901
Jonah?

15:44.444 --> 15:46.196
Jonah?

15:46.237 --> 15:48.239
Jonah, Jonah.

15:49.449 --> 15:50.909
Breathe, Jonah. Breathe.

15:50.950 --> 15:52.661
I don't want to fucking breathe.

15:52.702 --> 15:54.454
I don't want to fucking breathe!

15:54.496 --> 15:56.873
- I just want to fucking scream.
- Yes.

15:56.915 --> 15:59.042
I could fucking scream
right now at my safta.

15:59.084 --> 16:01.044
- Yes.
- Murray, Booty.

16:01.086 --> 16:02.504
They all have one thing
in common.

16:02.545 --> 16:04.185
You know what that is?
It's me. That's me.

16:04.214 --> 16:05.566
- I fucking killed them.
- No. No, you...

16:05.590 --> 16:06.651
No, I'm responsible for that.

16:06.675 --> 16:08.343
- No.
- No, I am. It's me.

16:08.385 --> 16:10.428
I'm a fucking curse.
I'm the Grim Reaper.

16:10.470 --> 16:13.223
- I'm a fucking...
- No, don't put
their deaths on you.

16:13.264 --> 16:14.808
Come on, they're Nazi...

16:14.849 --> 16:16.744
- They're Nazi monsters.
- Do you know how I feel inside?

16:16.768 --> 16:18.954
Do you know how I... do you
understand how I feel inside?

16:18.978 --> 16:20.146
Yes. I do.

16:20.188 --> 16:21.314
I feel like I'm burning.

16:21.356 --> 16:22.941
Like I'm on fucking fire.

16:22.982 --> 16:24.627
- I want to fucking explode
right now.
- Yes.

16:24.651 --> 16:26.528
I can't stop seeing them.

16:26.569 --> 16:27.862
I fucking hesitated.

16:27.904 --> 16:29.364
I got Booty killed.

16:29.406 --> 16:31.533
- I let that lady get away.
- All right,

16:31.574 --> 16:33.785
then why did you show mercy
to that monster?

16:33.827 --> 16:35.262
- Why? Why didn't you...
- I hesitated.

16:35.286 --> 16:36.931
- Shoot that woman...
- 'Cause I hesitated.

16:36.955 --> 16:38.891
- With a child in her arms?
- I fucking hesitated.

16:38.915 --> 16:41.018
-Why didn't you do it?
-'Cause I'm a fuck...
I'm a fuckup.

16:41.042 --> 16:43.104
- Jonah, tell me why! Why?
- I'm a fuckup. I'm a fuckup.

16:43.128 --> 16:45.255
-Why?!
-I did the right thing.
I did the right thing.

16:45.296 --> 16:47.382
I did what she would have
wanted me to do.

16:50.468 --> 16:53.054
That's right.

16:53.096 --> 16:54.681
You're right.

16:54.723 --> 16:57.851
And yet,
they keep fucking winning.

16:57.892 --> 16:59.519
They keep fucking winning.

16:59.561 --> 17:02.897
Why do they get to play
by their own set of rules?

17:02.939 --> 17:06.359
Why do the good guys always have
to do the fucking right thing?

17:06.401 --> 17:07.777
We don't.

17:07.819 --> 17:10.405
Why do you have that
in your head?

17:10.447 --> 17:14.284
You had this all your life,
this thing about the comic books

17:14.325 --> 17:16.327
and crusaders and heroes.

17:16.369 --> 17:18.997
Heroes made from ink.

17:19.038 --> 17:20.331
Not blood.

17:20.373 --> 17:22.333
Heroes made of parchment.

17:22.375 --> 17:23.835
Not flesh.

17:23.877 --> 17:25.336
Fantasies.

17:25.378 --> 17:27.338
Wishes.

17:27.380 --> 17:28.548
They're lies.

17:28.590 --> 17:30.425
Jonah, they are lies.

17:32.552 --> 17:35.346
You have in you...

17:35.388 --> 17:38.224
a fire that needs
to be released.

17:40.226 --> 17:43.062
Get ready to know what it is

17:43.104 --> 17:45.815
to be a hero in this world.

17:51.488 --> 17:54.115
But I have to tell you
something now.

17:55.158 --> 17:58.745
I have to tell you why...

17:58.787 --> 18:01.664
I was unworthy of your safta.

18:01.706 --> 18:03.833
♪ ♪

18:05.877 --> 18:08.671
One night, The Wolf
came into my room.

18:10.423 --> 18:13.468
He woke me up from my dream
and dragged me outside

18:13.510 --> 18:15.470
into the woods.

18:15.512 --> 18:17.096
You have a choice.

18:17.138 --> 18:19.224
You can choose...

18:19.265 --> 18:21.726
to kill this innocent man...

18:23.561 --> 18:25.313
or...

18:26.898 --> 18:29.067
I will kill Ruth
right where she stands.

18:29.108 --> 18:31.528
Don't, Meyer...

18:31.569 --> 18:33.613
don't let him win.

18:33.655 --> 18:36.366
Let him kill me instead.

18:36.407 --> 18:39.619
That's what I want. Please.

18:39.661 --> 18:42.372
- Kill me. Kill me!
- Shh. Hey, hey.

18:42.413 --> 18:43.957
- Hey. Hey.
- Kill me!

18:43.998 --> 18:46.084
- Shh, shh.
- It's my choice.

18:46.125 --> 18:48.169
Meyerleh. Meyer.

18:48.211 --> 18:50.088
- Meyer.
- Who are you going to choose,
huh?

18:50.129 --> 18:53.967
Choose me. Shoot me, Meyer.

18:54.008 --> 18:55.008
Meyer.

18:58.304 --> 18:59.973
Myer, no.

19:00.014 --> 19:01.850
Nie, Meyer, nie!

19:11.067 --> 19:12.861
It grew quiet.

19:14.988 --> 19:16.948
And the smoke billowed

19:16.990 --> 19:19.117
from my pistol.

19:32.755 --> 19:34.757
Meyerleh?

19:36.885 --> 19:38.428
Bring me the next one!

19:38.469 --> 19:41.055
But... it was only the start.

19:45.643 --> 19:47.103
How many?

19:47.145 --> 19:48.563
How many do you think
she's worth?

19:48.605 --> 19:49.856
No, Meyer!

19:56.237 --> 19:59.574
- Meyer. Meyer.
- How many?

20:03.036 --> 20:05.079
Please, Meyer.

20:05.121 --> 20:06.998
Meyer, choose me.

20:15.548 --> 20:17.550
And I said...

20:31.022 --> 20:34.192
Perhaps this is a story...

20:34.233 --> 20:37.737
that is not meant
to be told today.

20:37.779 --> 20:40.073
Today is for Murray.

20:40.114 --> 20:42.200
We must grieve for him.

20:42.241 --> 20:44.369
We should not desecrate that.

20:45.662 --> 20:48.247
And there will be time
for this story.

20:49.791 --> 20:52.001
It deserves time.

21:03.888 --> 21:07.558
I'd recognize
those hooker heels anywhere.

21:07.600 --> 21:10.019
Didn't the nuns raise us
to be chaste?

21:12.480 --> 21:13.898
Keeping up this act

21:13.940 --> 21:15.817
finally netted you
something valuable, huh?

21:15.858 --> 21:18.528
To be perfectly frank,
I'm still shocked

