37:56.525 --> 37:58.193
I need everything you have

37:58.235 --> 37:59.611
on von Braun.

37:59.653 --> 38:01.613
Oh, you're a spiritualist now?

38:01.655 --> 38:04.491
Well, you see, he died.

38:04.533 --> 38:06.535
- He died.
- Mm-hmm.

38:06.576 --> 38:08.245
You saw the body?

38:08.286 --> 38:10.580
We've heard many ghost stories

38:10.622 --> 38:13.291
of men bigger than Wernher.

38:13.333 --> 38:15.877
Yeah, y-you're
on a fool's errand, Meyer.

38:15.919 --> 38:17.629
What? What?
Come on, what do you want?

38:17.671 --> 38:19.214
What do you want?

38:19.256 --> 38:21.842
If he's dead, we go on a
wild fucking goose chase, right?

38:21.883 --> 38:23.343
Keeps us from knocking off

38:23.385 --> 38:25.053
another one of these
motherfuckers.

38:25.095 --> 38:27.073
You can go back to your whole
Atticus Finch routine.

38:27.097 --> 38:29.391
Isn't that what you want?

38:29.433 --> 38:30.809
You are Ruth's grandson.

38:30.851 --> 38:34.021
Mm.

38:36.481 --> 38:39.192
You desecrate her memory
by choosing this.

38:49.786 --> 38:54.499
All right, I'll give you
what you ask for...

38:54.541 --> 38:56.877
send you on your fantasy hunt.

38:56.918 --> 38:58.336
On one condition.

38:58.378 --> 39:00.422
That you never come to me again.

39:00.464 --> 39:03.050
All right?
Not for anything.

39:03.091 --> 39:06.094
We have a deal, brother.

39:06.136 --> 39:10.098
Meyer...

39:10.140 --> 39:14.269
remember, before the night fell,

39:14.311 --> 39:16.646
we were just people
listening to music,

39:16.688 --> 39:20.650
playing with our children,
telling stories.

39:20.692 --> 39:22.486
But we were chosen, Meyer.

39:22.527 --> 39:24.279
We were.

39:24.321 --> 39:27.699
Sometimes I wish we weren't,
but we were chosen.

39:27.741 --> 39:30.744
Now, perhaps this is God's
ultimate test.

39:30.786 --> 39:33.872
Not the slavery in Egypt,
or Rome, or the pogroms.

39:33.914 --> 39:36.416
Not even the Shoah.

39:39.377 --> 39:42.005
Perhaps this is
the greatest test of all...

39:42.047 --> 39:45.342
is what we choose to do now.

39:47.928 --> 39:51.056
Meyer, remember who we were.

39:51.098 --> 39:54.434
Remember who we are. Re...

40:02.776 --> 40:06.947
Thank you... for the facts.

40:08.365 --> 40:10.367
Let's go.

40:14.454 --> 40:17.332
Schidler Corp. 5623

40:17.374 --> 40:20.168
West Fifth...
That's what the file says.

40:20.210 --> 40:21.670
Million-dollar corporation
operates

40:21.711 --> 40:25.006
out of a fucking
bunion boutique?

40:37.978 --> 40:39.896
What'd Joe do,
hire a Coldwell Banker lady

40:39.938 --> 40:41.481
for an open house
at von Braun's?

40:41.523 --> 40:43.066
Let's go already.

40:43.108 --> 40:45.318
He needs to scope it out first.

40:45.360 --> 40:47.571
He'll be back soon enough.

40:49.906 --> 40:51.950
You stole from him,
from Wiesenthal.

40:51.992 --> 40:54.703
Files on The Wolf.
What'd you find in them?

40:54.744 --> 40:56.746
Not much.

40:56.788 --> 40:58.165
Your safta took the files.

40:58.206 --> 41:02.377
She wanted to learn more
about The Wolf.

41:02.419 --> 41:06.715
What Wiesenthal said
about her...

41:06.756 --> 41:09.676
I mean, it's bullshit, right?
It's-it's fucking bullshit.

41:09.718 --> 41:11.052
I'm not desecrating shit.

41:11.094 --> 41:13.305
- I'm fucking honoring her.
- Of course you are.

41:13.346 --> 41:14.723
What we're doing, it's...

41:14.764 --> 41:16.641
I mean, you said it.
You said it.

41:16.683 --> 41:19.394
It's... The Hunt is Jewish.

41:19.436 --> 41:21.354
And-and our forefathers
did it, too.

41:21.396 --> 41:23.440
They fought for their existence.

41:23.481 --> 41:24.983
They killed their enemies.

41:25.025 --> 41:26.735
They ended shit.

41:26.776 --> 41:29.446
Of course they did.

41:33.074 --> 41:34.868
How many people
did you kill that night?

41:42.459 --> 41:45.503
Eleven.

41:48.381 --> 41:51.009
Eleven men.

41:52.719 --> 41:55.639
Eleven innocent souls.

41:55.680 --> 41:58.934
In that moment, I made a choice.

41:58.975 --> 42:00.435
To protect the woman I love.

42:00.477 --> 42:03.647
And in doing that,

42:03.688 --> 42:06.691
I became a different creature.

42:08.526 --> 42:12.447
The Wolf had won,

42:12.489 --> 42:15.617
and I never saw
the sun rise again.

42:19.454 --> 42:21.456
It cost me my world.

42:23.500 --> 42:27.420
But it turned me toward the man

42:27.462 --> 42:29.714
I was destined to be.

42:29.756 --> 42:33.176
Now in darkness,

42:33.218 --> 42:35.512
I could protect the light.

42:35.553 --> 42:38.848
I became the night

42:38.890 --> 42:41.935
so that the day would live.

42:44.312 --> 42:47.482
That is the mark
of a hero, Jonah.

42:47.524 --> 42:50.568
Not the one who does
what is right,

42:50.610 --> 42:54.364
but the one who does...

42:54.406 --> 42:56.533
what is necessary.

43:07.294 --> 43:10.130
You sure you're gonna be okay
alone here, Ma?

43:10.171 --> 43:14.718
Yeah, darling, please, I'm fine.
You-you go.

43:14.759 --> 43:17.595
Don't forget to wear
that sweater.

43:17.637 --> 43:19.097
It's July, Ma.

43:19.139 --> 43:20.515
I know, but you know,

43:20.557 --> 43:23.560
they blast that air-conditioning
everywhere.

43:23.601 --> 43:25.145
Okay.

43:25.186 --> 43:27.939
You know Carol Smolinsky.

43:27.981 --> 43:30.692
She went into the movie
theater to see

43:30.734 --> 43:32.527
Herbie Goes to Monte Carlo.

43:32.569 --> 43:35.530
She left there with pneumonia.

43:35.572 --> 43:37.282
I'll wear the sweater, Ma.

43:37.324 --> 43:39.284
- Okay?
- Yeah.

43:39.326 --> 43:41.328
Good girl.

43:41.369 --> 43:44.539
You all right there?

43:44.581 --> 43:46.958
Yeah. Are you?

43:47.000 --> 43:48.376
- Oh, me?
- Yeah.

43:48.418 --> 43:50.670
I'm fine. Go, go, go.

43:53.423 --> 43:55.633
- Yeah.
- Okay.

43:58.345 --> 44:01.222
Hey, Ma. Love you.

44:16.196 --> 44:18.740
Well, you know,
Irene Schlosstein,

44:18.782 --> 44:22.077
she just could not
keep her mouth shut.

44:22.118 --> 44:24.371
And the waterworks.
It was like

44:24.412 --> 44:27.624
it was her husband's shiva.

44:27.665 --> 44:32.504
That Hymie Herschel, he-he
smelled up the whole apartment,

44:32.545 --> 44:36.257
of course, you know.

44:36.299 --> 44:41.179
And the insufferable
Eileen Shekenstein came,

44:41.221 --> 44:43.556
but you know,

44:43.598 --> 44:46.893
she-she gave me a nice hello,

44:46.935 --> 44:49.312
and that-that counts
for something.

44:49.354 --> 44:51.398
Yeah, it sure does.

44:51.439 --> 44:54.859
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

44:54.901 --> 44:57.237
- Oh, the rabbi...
- Oh.

44:57.278 --> 44:59.280
No, no, tell me
all about the rabbi. What?

44:59.322 --> 45:01.449
Well, he gave
a beautiful service.

45:01.491 --> 45:02.635
Yeah, you know what
the only perk is

45:02.659 --> 45:04.035
about being blown up to bits?

45:04.077 --> 45:05.412
I didn't have
to sit through that.

45:05.453 --> 45:08.498
Oh, please. You're just
such a wise-ass.

45:08.540 --> 45:11.960
Yes, well, some things,
Mindeleh, are eternal.

45:16.840 --> 45:21.136
Who is going to fix
that leak in the sink?

45:21.177 --> 45:23.847
You'll get a handyman.

45:23.888 --> 45:27.892
And who's going to change
the light bulbs?

45:27.934 --> 45:30.854
You'll ask the boys.

45:35.942 --> 45:38.611
Who is going...

45:38.653 --> 45:41.781
to put his arm
around me at night?

45:41.823 --> 45:46.327
Who is going to groan when
I pass a little gas,

45:46.369 --> 45:50.915
and rub my bunions and...

45:50.957 --> 45:55.420
Who is going to know
the stories, you know,

45:55.462 --> 45:58.840
that gave me these wrinkles?

45:58.882 --> 46:01.342
Who's going to watch over me?

46:01.384 --> 46:04.095
I will.

46:04.137 --> 46:05.555
I always will.

46:11.269 --> 46:13.104
Are you with him?

46:13.146 --> 46:14.898
I am.

46:17.400 --> 46:18.985
How does he look?

46:19.027 --> 46:20.653
Just as you remember him.

46:20.695 --> 46:22.697
Yeah?

46:24.782 --> 46:27.035
- Is he safe?
- Safe.

46:27.076 --> 46:29.871
- Is he happy?
- Oh, he's happy.

46:33.291 --> 46:35.293
Is he him?

46:37.212 --> 46:39.214
He's him.

46:47.222 --> 46:51.476
Does he forgive us
for what happened?

46:51.518 --> 46:54.187
And for living on...

46:54.229 --> 46:56.231
without him?

46:57.357 --> 46:59.526
Yeah, he does.

46:59.567 --> 47:01.569
But he misses you.

47:02.570 --> 47:04.531
He misses you.

47:04.572 --> 47:07.617
- He misses your scent.
- Ah.

47:07.659 --> 47:09.702
He misses your rugelach.

47:09.744 --> 47:11.788
And he misses the way

47:11.829 --> 47:14.040
you used to kiss him,

47:14.082 --> 47:16.793
even though he was pretending
to be sleeping.

47:19.462 --> 47:23.007
Mm. Would you like to see him?

47:25.051 --> 47:26.302
Murray.

47:26.344 --> 47:27.554
Yeah. Come.

47:27.595 --> 47:29.222
- Murray. Murray!
- Come, come.

47:29.264 --> 47:31.891
- I-I see him?
- Come.

47:39.357 --> 47:41.317
Where is he?

47:41.359 --> 47:43.361
- You'll see.
- Oh.

48:01.004 --> 48:03.047
Aaron?

48:03.089 --> 48:04.632
- Come.
- Ah.

48:04.674 --> 48:06.551
Aaron. Oh.

48:06.593 --> 48:09.971
Ketzeleh. Ketzeleh.

48:10.013 --> 48:13.016
Oh. Oh.

48:15.935 --> 48:18.062
Oh.

48:18.104 --> 48:20.106
I missed you, Mama.

48:20.148 --> 48:22.108
Oh.

48:22.150 --> 48:24.152
My boy,

48:24.193 --> 48:27.113
I missed you.

48:27.155 --> 48:29.949
Oh.

48:29.991 --> 48:33.411
Did you do all this?

48:33.453 --> 48:36.873
So that when you and Tata came,
you'd feel at home.

48:36.914 --> 48:40.043
It's beautiful.

48:40.084 --> 48:42.295
Oh, it's so beautiful.

48:42.337 --> 48:44.881
Do you want
to make something, Mama?

48:44.922 --> 48:46.883
Oh.

48:46.924 --> 48:49.260
I'd rather not dare.

48:49.302 --> 48:53.097
Whatever I make...
It will not compare,

48:53.139 --> 48:55.099
because many years ago,

48:55.141 --> 49:00.647
I already made the most
beautiful thing of all.

49:05.735 --> 49:10.073
Mindeleh, it's time to go now.

49:10.114 --> 49:12.200
Yes. Say yes.

49:12.241 --> 49:14.202
Before it's too late.

49:14.243 --> 49:18.164
Mindy, it's not time
for you to stay here with us.

49:18.206 --> 49:20.458
- Not yet.
- Mm.

49:20.500 --> 49:22.502
Aaron.

49:22.543 --> 49:26.255
Aaron, you say goodbye
to your mama.

49:26.297 --> 49:28.257
Yeah.

49:33.638 --> 49:35.473
- Yeah.
- Time.

49:35.515 --> 49:37.850
Come.

49:37.892 --> 49:40.186
Hey, Aaron, Aaron?

49:41.979 --> 49:44.357
Go.

49:44.399 --> 49:46.150
Come.

49:46.192 --> 49:47.610
Ooh.

49:51.989 --> 49:53.991
Yeah? Come.

49:56.119 --> 49:59.706
You don't have
to worry about him.

49:59.747 --> 50:03.000
I will take care of him,
I will never let him go.

50:05.002 --> 50:07.004
I know that.

50:08.172 --> 50:10.383
You-you never did.

50:12.969 --> 50:15.638
And he will take care of you

50:15.680 --> 50:19.892
for a time
until I see you again.

50:19.934 --> 50:21.936
Yeah.

50:31.988 --> 50:33.948
One last thing.

50:33.990 --> 50:36.576
Aaron asked

50:36.617 --> 50:40.913
that you show to Moritz mercy.

50:40.955 --> 50:43.499
That is his wish.

50:57.430 --> 51:01.809
You have a guardian angel,
Moritz.

51:01.851 --> 51:05.438
An angel, I say.

51:05.480 --> 51:07.231
Yeah.

51:07.273 --> 51:10.026
- Huh.
- You-you deserved

51:10.067 --> 51:12.403
so much worse.

